The paper deals with the Maximum Independent Set problem on a specific class of graphs, namely the $B_1$-EPG graphs, which are a subclass of EPG graphs. EPG graphs are a topic in computational geometry and graph theory, which suggests that cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) are likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the approximability and fixed parameter tractability of the problem, indicating that cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) are also possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper presents a polynomial-time algorithm for a restricted version of the problem, which suggests that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a possible sub-category.
